content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Add a Checkbox input element on a FlexCard to enable users to select or unselect a checkbox. Configure properties and custom attributes, add an action, and add conditions.

From the Build panel, click Inputs, and drag the Checkbox element onto the canvas.
Configure properties common to all Input elements:
In Field Binding, bind the value of the input element to an existing or new data field.
Check Required if the user must enter or select a value for this input element.
Check Read-only to disable the ability to modify the input values.
In Help Text, enter helpful text about the purpose of the input field.

In Checkbox Label, enter the label that appears next to the checkbox.
Check Default Value to enable the checkbox by default.
Configure additional properties available to the element:
Click + Add New in the Custom Attributes section.
Select an attribute from the dropdown and enter a value for it.
To execute an action when a user selects or unselects the checkbox, click + Add Action.

Checkbox Input element properties are configurable in the Properties panel when you select a Checkbox element in the FlexCard Designer.
title: Adding Checkbox Input Elements in FlexCards
